commit.message: Fix compile error due to wrong #includes.

Add a CommonMark version of the manual.

This uses the GFM table extension. Pandoc can be used to create a HTML
file:

    pandoc -s --columns=1000 --css=manual.css manual.md -o manual.html
Update the copy of the GPL version 2.

Remove the NSIS and RPM .spec files.

These files are not kept up to date, so it's better to not have them at
all in this repository.

Revive the map editor.

The graphical map editor is now working again. It allows changing map tiles,
and allows adding and removing enemies. For anything else, one has to
modify the YAML files manually.
Add to defEnemy[] array in the normal order.
Allow changing the location of the data files at runtime.
Fix loading line definitions from map files.
Prevent trains from added to the map twice.
Crop map data in map files.
Fix a segfault when reading spawnpoints with no subtype.

Move frame rate limiting into graphics.updateScreen().

Try to do a precise sleep to limit ourselves to at most 62.5 Hz.
This should give a smooth experience on G-SYNC/FreeSync monitors, and falls
back to 60 Hz on most fixed-frequency monitors.
Use Meson as the build system.
Use yaml-cpp to parse the YAML datafiles.
